Detectives have camped at the Coast General Hospital waiting to arrest Kilifi Deputy Governor Gideon Saburi. Saburi has been discharged after recovering from Covid-19. However, he is still holed up at the isolation centre at the CGH. Police told the Star they arrived at the hospital as early as 9 am. "He says he has sent for another pair of clothes but we think it is a delaying tactic," said a detective, who sought anonymity. Health CS Mutahi Kagwe on Thursday announced that Saburi had recovered from the virus and will be arrested and charged for refusing to self-quarantine upon return from an official trip on Germany on March 7. More to follow...